 A GROUP, the Grand Council of Yoruba Youths, has hailed elder statesman and Afenifere leader, Pa Reuben Fasoranti, as he turned 94. The President-General, Comrade Awa Bamiji, also congratulated a freedom fighter and publisher of Ovation Magazine, Dele Momodu, as he celebrated his 60th birthday. He described him as a pride of African journalism and a trailblazer of an uncommon dimension. The body celebrated anti-corruption Czar, Comrade Debo Adeniran, as he turned 60, saying “he is a fighter in whom we have a hope of a better country as far as anti-corruption crusade is concerned.” It endorsed Comrade Amitolu Shittu’s appointment as the Director-General of Amotekun Corps in Osun State, noting that the appointment is not only timely, but also signals a new dawn when the good people of Osun State can go to bed with their two eyes closed. 